My meme

My meme can be explained as ‘RS vs VS’ and created it because both got the word ‘Studio’ included and my meme is original.

library(magick)

#Read dog images
sad_dog <- image_read("https://canna-pet.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/dog-depression-canna-pet-e1494862902380.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(430)

happy_dog <- image_read("https://www.rd.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/GettyImages-1007461064-scaled-e1617228878455.jpg?fit=696,465") %>%
  image_scale(430)

#Create blank image with text
rs_text <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                          height = 323, 
                          color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "RStudio",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 70,
                 gravity = "center")

vs_text <- image_blank(width = 300, 
                         height = 287, 
                         color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Visual\nStudio",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 70,
                 gravity = "center")

#Append dog image and blank image
row1 <- c(sad_dog, rs_text) %>%
  image_append()

row2 <- c(happy_dog, vs_text) %>%
  image_append()

#Append final images
meme <- c(row1, row2) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

#Save meme as an image
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

My animated GIF was motivated by one of GIF in lab exercise and added cat meme after ‘STATS220’ and my meme is original except the picture of cat.

library(magick)

# creating each frame
first_frame1 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "S", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

first_frame2 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "T", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(600) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

first_frame3 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "A", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(700) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

first_frame4 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "T", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(800) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

first_frame5 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "S", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(900) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

first_frame6 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(800) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

first_frame7 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "2", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(700) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

first_frame8 <- image_blank(width = 500, height = 500) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "0", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(600) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

first_frame9 <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/originals/96/9b/19/969b19d4dd1d3e48b6682327579eef1e.png") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# putting the frames in order using a vector
first_frames <- c(first_frame1, first_frame2, first_frame3, first_frame4, 
                  first_frame5, first_frame6, first_frame7, first_frame8, first_frame9)

# creating an animation
animation <- image_animate(first_frames, fps = 2)

#Save animated GIF
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
